-- PRESS DIGEST -China - June 17
-- By Shanghai Newsroom
-- Mon Jun 16, 2014 09:44PM EDT
-- None



SHANGHAI, June 17 (Reuters) - Chinese newspapers available in Beijing and Shanghai carried the following stories on Tuesday. Reuters has not checked the stories and does not vouch for their accuracy.

SHANGHAI SECURITIES NEWS   - Four banks -- Bank of China Ltd <601988.SS> <3988.HK>, Industrial and Commercial Bank of China Ltd <601398.SS> <1398.HK>, Shanghai Pudong Development Bank Co Ltd <600000.SS> and Bank of Shanghai -- have been given approval to open "free trade" account in Shanghai's free trade zone as part of a pilot scheme to facilitate capital flows.  CHINA SECURITIES JOURNAL - The China Securities Regulatory Commission's Chairman, Xiao Gang, said the regulator would strengthen rules on delisting by Chinese listed companies. - Qianhai, a special economic zone in the southern city of Shenzhen, will publish rules as early as this month that will grant Hong Kong companies national treatment as part of a scheme to strengthen cooperation between the two neighbouring cities.  CHINA DAILY - Judicial system reform is the only way to make rule of law a reality, and a pilot scheme for nominating judges and prosecutors and giving them life-long responsibility for the cases they handle will increase the independence and autonomy of the judiciary, the newspaper said in an editorial.